  "text": "To guarantee the inducible expression of the eptC gene, plasmid pBAD18-Cm-eptC was constructed and electroporated into the two K. pneumoniae mutants 52145∆wabH [CITATION_1] and K. pneumoniae 52145∆wabG [CITATION_2] . LPS from K. pneumoniae 52145∆wabG (+pBAD18-Cm-eptC grown under arabinose promoter inducing conditions) migration was slower than that of LPS from K. pneumoniae 52145∆wabG grown under the same conditions ( Figure 4, lanes 2 and 3) . Similar results were obtained when comparing LPS from K. pneumoniae 52145∆wabH (+pBAD18-Cm-eptC) and K. pneumoniae 52145∆wabH always grown under arabinose promoter inducing conditions ( The spectrometry (ESI-MS) spectrum of K. pneumoniae 52145∆wabG core oligosaccharide showed a pseudo-molecular ion (M-H)-at m/z 783.37 which was in agreement with the calculated average molecular weight (783.67) of the expected molecular structure, with one hexose, two heptoses and one Kdo unit as previously reported [CITATION_3] . The identical result was obtained when the core oligosaccharide of K. pneumoniae 52145∆wabG (+pBAD18-Cm-eptC) was obtained from cells grown under non-induced conditions. To unambiguously test the eptC requirement for PEtN transfer, LPS from cells of 52145∆wabG (+pBAD18-Cm-eptC) grown under arabinose promoter inducing conditions was isolated from dried cells by phenol-water extraction and purified (see Experimental Section). Mild acid degradation of this LPS resulted in a core fraction purified by gel-permeation chromatography on Sephadex G-50. High-resolution negative ion electrospray ionization mass spectrum of this fraction showed a major [ spectrum showed one signal for a monophosphate group at  0.5. The 1 H-NMR spectrum of the OS was assigned using two-dimensional COSY and TOCSY experiments, and then the 13 C-NMR spectrum was assigned using a two-dimensional 1 H-, [CITATION_4] C-HSQC experiment. The assigned 1 H-and 13 C-NMR chemical shifts (Table 1) were in full agreement with the carbohydrate backbone composition and structure expected for the core OS derived from K. pneumoniae wabG deletion mutant [CITATION_5] . ",
